Create function used in HSE compiler to do the following:

char* new_distribution(  int LOWERA, int UPPERA, char* distA,
                         int LOWERB, int UPPERB, char* distb )

Returns a new string representing a new distribution that is a combination
of the two passed in distribution.  If the two distributions 'cannot' be
combined,
the function should return NULL.

For distA and distb = Uniform:

   new_distribution = U( distA.LOWER + distB.LOWER, distA.UPPER + distB.UPPER )

For distA and distb NULL 

   new_distribution = U( LOWERA + LOWERB, UPPERA + UPPERB )

For distA or distb NULL AND distA or distB Uniform

   dist = (distA==NULL) ? distB : distA;
   LOWER = (distA==NULL) ? LOWERA : LOWERB;
   UPPPER = (distA==NULL) ? UPPERA : UPPERB;
   new_distribution = U( dist.LOWER + LOWER, dist.UPPER + UPPER )

For distA and distB NORMAL

   new_distribution = N( distA.mean + distB.mean, distA.std + distB.std )


ELSE
 
   new_distribution = NULL


NOTE: It is not possible to combine Singular distributions with anything.  
It is also not possible to combine a Normals with anything but normals.

